<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-157-067 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 795 075</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  May 13 1991 v220 n19 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Carriers urged to cross borders. (International communications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>France Telecom Chmn Marcel Roulet believes that telecommunicationscompanies must consider entering foreign markets if they wish toachieve future growth.andP;  France Telecom, which is planning to takeadvantage of foreign markets, expects to obtain 10 percent of itsrevenues from international operations besides internationaltraffic by 2000.andP;  A large part of the firm's foreign investmentactivity will be in mobile communications and value-addedservices.andP;  Several countries have indicated that they will welcomeforeign competition, including the US, Japan, France, andAustralia.andP;  Developing countries have warned telecommunicationsfirms not to overlook their need for basic telephone service.andO;Telecommunications firms that plan to expand internationallyshould establish clear goals and focus on their core competencies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   France Telecom (Foreign operations).andO;Topic:     Communications IndustryInternational CommunicationsForeign InvestmentForeign CompetitionGrowthTelecommunications ServicesMarket EntryDeveloping Countries.andO;Person:    Roulet, Marcel (Management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>